                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/6324.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-02-23T17:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 23, 1913—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>30. I think the effect would be excellent if, in case the atmosphere clears
                    measurably in the next two days, the Department would send to this city the
                    commanding officers of our boats in Vera Cruz with the marines and such sailors
                    as may be deemed advisable. I can make the necessary arrangement here, if the
                    Department approves my recommendation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
